info.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 30 at 3:27PM MST until January 31 at 11:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 11 PM THIS EVENING TO 11 PM MST MONDAY... * WHAT...West winds 40 to 65 mph with gusts up to 90 mph expected. * WHERE...North Laramie Range, Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County, East Platte County, South Laramie Range and South Laramie Range Foothills. * WHEN...From 11 PM this evening to 11 PM MST Monday. * IMPACTS...Travel will be difficult, especially for high profile vehicles. An extreme blow over risk will be present for high profile vehicles. Winds of this magnitude can lead to property damage.
info.instruction: A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts of 58 mph or more can lead to property damage.
